<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1947-03-21T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1947-03-21T00:00:00-05:00" n="572" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d572">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00119 Control (Italy)/3–2147:
                                Airgram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Italy</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Dunn</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Rome</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1947-03-21">March 21,
                                    1947</date>.</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>
                                <gloss target="#t_A1">A–458</gloss>. Reference Embassy’s secret
                                    <gloss target="#t_A1">A–404</gloss>, March 7, 1947.<note n="1" xml:id="d572fn1">Not printed.</note> Effective 2359 hours, March
                                15, 1947, Italian Military Affairs Section, <gloss target="#t_AFHQ1">AFHQ</gloss>, was abolished. The Land, Naval and Air Forces Sub
                                Sections have now become Italian Land Forces, Italian Naval and
                                Italian Air Forces Branches of <gloss target="#t_AFHQ1">AFHQ</gloss>, respectively.</p>
                            <p>Admiral Stone terminated his official connection with <gloss target="#t_AFHQ1">AFHQ</gloss> as Chief of the Italian Military
                                Affairs Section on March 15, 1947.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Dunn</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>